title: For Sale/Trade:  Smith and Wesson S&W SD9ve 9mm 16+1 pistol
postcontent:
$400obo or Trade. Brand new in box, unfired. These are $409 plus tax at the store I got it from. there's nothing wrong with the gun, it's just not what i need at the moment!

This gun gets really good reviews everywhere online, i suggest checking some of them out. I have no doubt that this is a good, reliable gun. Comparisons found it to be as reliable, or even more reliable than the Glock 9mm that it is VERY similar to. (Glock sued S&W for the sigma design that this gun was derived from). The SD9ve is said to improve upon Smith and Wesson's Sigma and SW9 pistols, the predecessors to this gun. 

I've heard people gripe about the trigger, but this is the newest iteration of the pistol with the best trigger. It was the Sigmas and SW9s that had the stiff, rough trigger pull. It's fairly heavy (called a "self-defense" trigger, i think it's about 8lbs. if i remember correctly) but not so heavy it's hard to shoot. I personally like it, as do others i know who own SD9VEs. Serves as a safety feature as this gun is meant to be carried loaded for self defense. Great for a CCW if you want something you can fit your whole hand on. Stainless slide and black polymer frame.

Includes two 16 round original mags, a cable lock, original box and paperwork (everything that comes with it brand new!). Made in the USA!

Open to trades and cash offers- I paid $409 plus tax, but i realize i won't get all of that out of reselling the gun. That said, i see no reason to take a large loss on the gun- i'm not desperate for the money. i just want to see what else is out there! Thanks for looking!

call or text 812-230-two six three five, any time. text preferred, i'm busy a lot but feel free to call if that's what you prefer.
